---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Smeg Refrigerator Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "Smeg refrigerator repair across SoCal, FAB28/32/38 retro, FAB50 French Door, built-in columns. Italian Bermani family since 1948. $89 dx.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/smeg-refrigerator-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What does Smeg actually stand for, and is it really still Italian?",
    a: "Yes, still Italian, still family-owned, and \"Smeg\" is an acronym. Smalterie Metallurgiche Emiliane Guastalla, literally \"Emilian Metallurgical Enamel Works of Guastalla\", founded in 1948 in Guastalla, Italy by Vittorio Bermani. The company is still owned and operated by the Bermani family across three generations of leadership. Guastalla is the same Emilia-Romagna town that's home to Bertazzoni; two of Italy's best-known family-owned appliance manufacturers come out of the same town. Smeg has no conglomerate parent. For service in LA: parts chain runs through Smeg USA's authorized distribution with factory sourcing from Guastalla, typical 2–4 week lead times on standard components, 4–8 weeks for color-specific FAB exterior finishes."
  },
  {
    q: "The FAB refrigerator with the 1950s look, when did Smeg start making those?",
    a: "The FAB line launched in 1997 and has become the most recognizable retro-design refrigerator in the luxury category globally. The FAB aesthetic references 1950s American-kitchen styling, rounded corners, chrome trim, curvaceous silhouette, and Smeg's signature color palette (Cream, Pastel Blue, Pastel Green, Black, Red, 60+ other colors including custom). The refrigeration architecture inside is contemporary Italian engineering, auto-defrost, electronic temperature control, LED lighting, energy-efficient sealed system, but the exterior is unmistakably period-specific. For service, the iconic exterior matters: our techs photograph the chrome trim, handle hardware, and badge placement before any repair that involves exterior hardware, and reinstall preserves the factory finish. Damage to the FAB exterior requires color-matched replacement panels from the Guastalla factory; lead times run 4–8 weeks on color-exact sourcing."
  },
  {
    q: "FAB28 vs FAB32 vs FAB38 vs FAB50, what's the difference for service?",
    a: "The number indicates approximate width in centimeters and the broad size class. FAB28 is the compact single-door (about 10.3 cu ft, under-counter-adjacent). FAB32 is the narrow bottom-freezer (about 11.3 cu ft). FAB38 is the larger single-door with small freezer compartment (about 12.4 cu ft). FAB50 is the French Door two-door-top-single-freezer-bottom configuration, the retro look scaled up to full-size kitchen-dominant fridge. Service architecture is broadly similar across FAB sizes (sealed system components share a family, gaskets differ by size, retro trim hardware scales with the body), but FAB50 service is more involved because the French Door layout adds door-hinge and alignment work that the single-door FAB sizes don't have. Standard service costs on gasket and refrigeration-side repair are comparable across the range; FAB50 hinge and alignment work runs slightly higher."
  },
  {
    q: "Can you color-match the FAB door if it gets scratched or damaged?",
    a: "Yes, through Smeg USA's parts channel. The FAB color-finish program runs through Guastalla, when a panel is damaged from a move, cabinet install, or kitchen activity, the replacement panel is ordered in the exact matched color from the factory. Lead times are 4–8 weeks on color-matched exterior parts; standard stainless or Cream panels with higher production volume occasionally land faster. Our protocol: document the damage, confirm the exact color code from the interior factory sticker, coordinate the factory order through Smeg USA, install when delivered. Interior service on a FAB (gaskets, hinges, refrigeration cycle) doesn't depend on the exterior finish and runs at normal pace."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service the modern Smeg built-in column refrigerators, not just the FAB retro?",
    a: "Yes. Smeg's modern built-in column refrigerator line covers 24\" and 30\" widths, panel-ready or stainless finish, and is a legitimate architect-spec choice for kitchens that want Italian design language without the FAB retro aesthetic. Service profile on the built-in columns is closer to our other Italian-luxury columns (Bertazzoni, Fulgor Milano Distinto) than to the FAB, variable-speed compressor, multi-zone cooling, panel-ready alignment with the Smeg offset gauge. Less common in LA than FAB but real; we service both platforms. Column installs typically in Hollywood Hills modernist and certain Westside contemporary renovations."
  },
  {
    q: "Our FAB28 cream refrigerator isn't cooling, is this a common failure?",
    a: "Cooling failure on FAB can come from several places and our diagnostic order depends on what the symptom is describing. If the compressor isn't running at all: check for power, thermostat setpoint, and cold-control switch. If the compressor runs but doesn't cool: check refrigerant charge (rare, sealed-system leaks on FAB are uncommon), condenser airflow (dust buildup in the rear grille reduces heat rejection), or starter relay failure (relatively common on FAB age 6–10 years). If it cools partially: thermostat drift, gasket compression loss letting warm air in, or door-switch issue leaving an LED on that's adding heat load. Our techs run this in order; most FAB cooling calls resolve at the relay or thermostat level without sealed-system work. Relay replacement $180–$280. Thermostat $220–$360. Condenser clean + diagnostic $160–$260."
  },
  {
    q: "Smeg small appliances, kettles, toasters, mixers, do you service those too?",
    a: "No. Smeg's small-appliance line (kettles, toasters, espresso machines, stand mixers, blenders) is a separate product category from the major appliances. Small appliances are not in our service scope, we focus on refrigeration, ovens, ranges, dishwashers, and laundry. For small-appliance service the recommended path is Smeg USA's authorized small-appliance service network or replacement under Smeg's small-appliance warranty. Our scope on Smeg is specifically the refrigeration, cooking, and dishwasher lineup, the major-appliance categories."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Smeg refrigerator repair typically cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Common Smeg bands: door gasket (FAB28/32/38 single-door) $180–$320; door gasket (FAB50 French Door) $220–$380; gasket on built-in column $280–$460; starter relay replacement $180–$280; thermostat / cold-control $220–$360; condenser clean and diagnostic $160–$260; condenser fan motor $260–$440; evaporator defrost heater $280–$460; FAB hinge adjustment $180–$340; built-in column hinge re-shim $240–$420; main control board (on newer FAB with electronic controls) $420–$680; compressor replacement (post-warranty) $900–$1,600 depending on size and refrigerant; color-matched exterior panel replacement, quoted individually (4–8 week factory lead). FAB pricing runs slightly lower than built-in column pricing because the refrigeration architecture is smaller; FAB50 pricing sits between the two."
  },
  {
    q: "Smeg FAB is popular in entertaining kitchens, pool cabanas, home bars, can you service one installed outside?",
    a: "Only in fully enclosed, climate-controlled secondary spaces. FAB is rated as a residential indoor appliance; installation outdoors or in open-air cabanas voids the factory warranty and creates reliability issues we routinely see when clients try to use a FAB this way. Electronic controls suffer from humidity exposure, the stainless interior develops corrosion, and the sealed refrigeration cycle wasn't designed for the ambient temperature swings of an outdoor-adjacent install. For outdoor-kitchen refrigeration in Malibu, Pacific Palisades, Newport Coast installs, we recommend a dedicated outdoor-rated refrigerator (brands like DCS, True Residential Outdoor, or U-Line outdoor). We'll service a FAB in an enclosed pool-house kitchen that's climate-controlled; we won't recommend trying to salvage one used in a true outdoor or semi-outdoor install once the environmental damage has accumulated."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service FAB refrigerators imported from Europe before Smeg launched the US line?",
    a: "Case-by-case, and we'll tell you honestly before we agree to the work. Smeg USA launched the US-market FAB line with US-electrical-spec (120V/60Hz) compressors and US-certification on the electronics. Some FAB units in LA kitchens are European-spec imports from dealers that brought them in before or alongside the official US channel, these typically run on 220V (requiring a transformer) or have 220V-native compressors that wear faster on US transformer power. Parts availability on European-spec FAB is limited: Smeg USA's US parts channel carries US-SKU components, and European-SKU replacements require international sourcing. Our techs can diagnose European-spec FAB and do minor work; major refrigeration-side repair on an imported-spec unit often doesn't pencil against replacement with a US-SKU FAB. Bring any purchase documentation to the first visit, we verify the spec before committing to a major repair."
  },

    {
      q: "Where can I find the official Smeg manual or warranty information?",
      a: `Our technicians work independently of Smeg's factory service network - we're often faster and available same-day in Southern California.`
    },
  ];

const schemaJsons = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, Smeg Refrigerator Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical,
    "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL,
    "priceRange": "$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "serviceType": "Smeg Refrigerator Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Smeg refrigerator repair across Los Angeles, FAB 50s retro refrigerators (FAB28, FAB32, FAB38, FAB50 French Door), modern built-in columns, color-matched exterior panel service via Guastalla factory. Italian family-owned Bermani since 1948. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": {
      "@type": "Offer",
      "priceSpecification": {
        "@type": "PriceSpecification",
        "price": "89.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD",
        "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": f.q,
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a }
    }))
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Smeg", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/smeg/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Smeg Refrigerator Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">
    {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
    ))}
  </Fragment>

  <div class="call-banner">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>Smeg FAB refrigerator acting up? Same-day service across LA:</span>
      <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
          <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Smeg › Refrigerator Repair</div>
          <h1>Smeg Refrigerator Repair</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            Smeg is the 77-year-old Italian family manufacturer from Guastalla, the same Emilia-Romagna town that
            produces Bertazzoni, still family-owned by the Bermani family, still making the iconic FAB retro
            refrigerator that launched in 1997 and has become the most recognizable retro-design fridge in the
            world. Our techs service the Smeg refrigeration lineup across LA: FAB28, FAB32, FAB38 single-door retro;
            FAB50 French Door retro; modern built-in columns. Concentrations in Silver Lake, Echo Park, Venice,
            Hollywood Hills, and vintage-modern kitchens across the Westside. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential
            diagnostic waived with repair.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-cta">
            <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
            <a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="hero-facts">
            <li><b>FAB platform expertise</b>, retro-finish preservation, US-SKU vs European-spec diagnosis</li>
            <li><b>Color-matched exterior panels</b>, Guastalla factory sourcing, 4–8 week factory lead</li>
            <li><b>Italian Bermani family since 1948</b>, independent, no conglomerate parent</li>
            <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
          </ul>
        </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span>
      <span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span>
      <span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Smeg in LA, retro-design fridge with real Italian heritage</h2>
      <p>
        Smeg was founded in 1948 in Guastalla, Italy, by Vittorio Bermani, the name is an acronym for Smalterie
        Metallurgiche Emiliane Guastalla, "Emilian Metallurgical Enamel Works of Guastalla." 77 years later the
        Bermani family still owns the company, and the Guastalla factory still produces the appliances. That
        heritage matters to a lot of LA Smeg owners: the retro-design aesthetic isn't a marketing-agency costume;
        it's a 1948 Italian enamelling heritage that genuinely predates the mass-market retro-appliance category by
        decades.
      </p>
      <p>
        Smeg refrigeration in LA is concentrated around the FAB line, the 1997-launched retro refrigerator that
        Smeg reintroduced to capture 1950s American-kitchen styling in a modern Italian-engineered package. FAB
        installs appear across Silver Lake and Echo Park vintage-modern kitchens (where the retro aesthetic fits
        the mid-century architectural idiom), Venice and Santa Monica design-forward kitchens, and an increasing
        number of pool-house and entertainment-space installs in Beverly Hills and Malibu where a homeowner wanted
        a color-pop statement in a secondary kitchen. Modern Smeg built-in columns are less common but present in
        certain Hollywood Hills contemporary kitchens where the architect specified Smeg over the more-conventional
        Italian built-in brands.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Smeg refrigerator failures our techs see most often</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Pattern data from our Smeg FAB and built-in-column coverage across LA. The FAB platform is mature (28 years
        in market since 1997) so long-term failure patterns are well-understood. Built-in columns are newer and
        follow Italian luxury-column patterns.
      </p>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>FAB starter relay failure, compressor won't start</h3>
        <p>
          Most-common FAB call we run. Symptom: compressor buzzes briefly then stops, or won't start at all. On
          FAB units age 6–10 years the compressor starter relay is the common failure point, cheap part, moderate
          labor (the compressor is reasonably accessible on FAB), and a fast fix. Meter the relay, swap it if
          it tests bad. $180–$280 typical.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>FAB thermostat / cold-control drift</h3>
        <p>
          Older FAB units with mechanical cold-control dials (pre-electronic-control generations) occasionally
          drift, the setpoint at "4" doesn't produce the temperature it used to. Fix is cold-control replacement.
          Newer FAB with electronic temperature display has a different failure pattern (controller board vs. dial)
          but symptom is similar. $220–$360.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Condenser grille dust buildup, FAB rear airflow</h3>
        <p>
          FAB's condenser coil lives at the rear of the unit, often with limited clearance to the cabinet behind.
          Dust and pet hair accumulate in the coil fins over years and reduce heat rejection; the compressor works
          harder to maintain temperature and eventually can't keep up on warm summer days. Clean the condenser,
          check refrigeration performance, inform the homeowner of the maintenance interval going forward. $160–$260.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>FAB gasket compression loss at 8–12 years</h3>
        <p>
          The rubber gasket on the FAB door compresses over time; past 8–10 years of daily use, the seal weakens
          and warm room air leaks into the fridge. Symptoms include temperature creep in summer, condensation on
          the door frame, and the compressor running longer cycles. Gasket replacement $180–$320 depending on FAB
          size.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Color-matched exterior panel damage, Guastalla factory sourcing</h3>
        <p>
          The FAB's signature color finish is beautiful and when damaged, from a move, cabinet install, or
          kitchen-renovation mishap, it requires color-matched replacement from the Guastalla factory through
          Smeg USA's parts channel. Lead times 4–8 weeks on color-exact sourcing. Standard stainless or Cream
          finishes with higher production volume occasionally land faster (2–4 weeks). Interior service doesn't
          depend on exterior finish.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Built-in column alignment and sensor service</h3>
        <p>
          Modern Smeg built-in column refrigerators (separate from FAB) follow the same failure profile as other
          Italian luxury columns, panel-ready alignment drift at 12–24 months on heavy custom panels, zone sensor
          drift on multi-compartment architecture, standard gasket and hinge patterns. Service protocols match our
          broader Italian-luxury column training; parts through Smeg USA authorized channel.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Smeg US refrigerator lines we service</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Two major refrigerator categories in the US Smeg lineup: the signature FAB retro line (four sizes), and
        modern built-in columns. Small-appliance Smeg (toasters, kettles, mixers) is out of scope.
      </p>
      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>FAB28, compact single-door retro</h3>
          <p>Roughly 10.3 cu ft, single-door with small internal freezer shelf. Under-counter-adjacent size. Common
          in entertainment spaces, pool houses, pantries, and secondary kitchens. 60+ color options plus stainless.
          Icon of the retro-fridge category.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>FAB32, narrow bottom-freezer retro</h3>
          <p>Roughly 11.3 cu ft, narrower footprint with a bottom-freezer drawer. Popular in urban condo kitchens
          (Westside, Silver Lake) where full-size fridge dimensions don't fit.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>FAB38, larger single-door retro</h3>
          <p>Roughly 12.4 cu ft, larger FAB single-door with separate freezer compartment. The "main fridge" FAB
          size for households that want the retro aesthetic as the primary kitchen fridge.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>FAB50, French Door retro</h3>
          <p>The retro look scaled up. French Door top with single freezer drawer bottom. Full-size kitchen-
          dominant configuration. Service profile slightly more complex than smaller FAB sizes because French
          Door adds door-hinge and alignment work.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Modern built-in columns</h3>
          <p>24" and 30" built-in column refrigerators and freezers in contemporary Italian design language (not
          retro). Panel-ready or stainless. Variable-speed compressor, multi-zone cooling. Less common in LA than
          FAB but genuine part of the Smeg lineup.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>60+ FAB color palette</h3>
          <p>Cream (the iconic one), Pastel Blue, Pastel Green, Black, Red, plus 60-plus other colors including
          Union Jack, Stars-and-Stripes, and custom-color options. Color-matched exterior panel replacement sourced
          from the Guastalla factory with 4–8 week lead.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Smeg FAB vs Big Chill vs other retro-category brands</h2>
      <p>
        Smeg FAB has two direct retro-category competitors across our service area: Big Chill (Colorado-based retro
        refrigerator specialist) and a handful of Italian boutique retro brands. Here's the positioning.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Smeg FAB</b>, Italian-manufactured in Guastalla, Bermani family-owned since 1948, 60+ color palette,
        global distribution with US-SKU parts channel through Smeg USA. 1997 FAB launch makes the platform mature;
        service technology and parts availability are well-established. LA installs concentrated in design-forward
        kitchens and entertainment spaces.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Big Chill</b>, US retro-refrigerator brand (Boulder, CO). Similar visual category but manufactured
        differently; currently not a dedicated combo page on our site but serviceable if you have one.
      </p>
      <p>
        For LA households choosing between retro options: Smeg FAB has the longer manufacturing heritage, Italian-
        family-owned backing, and the broader color palette. Our techs service both. Smeg's US-market maturity
        gives it the edge on parts availability and service network.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>What Smeg refrigerator repair typically costs</h2>
      <p class="intro">Parts pricing runs lower than column luxury brands because the FAB architecture is more
      accessible. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
      <table class="price-table">
        <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Flat, waived if repair is authorized same visit</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Compressor starter relay (FAB)</td><td>$180 – $280</td><td>Common 6–10 year FAB service</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Thermostat / cold-control (FAB)</td><td>$220 – $360</td><td>Mechanical or electronic by generation</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Condenser clean + diagnostic</td><td>$160 – $260</td><td>Rear-coil maintenance</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket (FAB28/32/38)</td><td>$180 – $320</td><td>Size-specific profile, Smeg USA channel</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket (FAB50 French Door)</td><td>$220 – $380</td><td>French Door-specific</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket (built-in column)</td><td>$280 – $460</td><td>Column profile, taller door</td></tr>
        <tr><td>FAB hinge adjustment</td><td>$180 – $340</td><td>Alignment drift, closer tension</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Built-in column hinge re-shim</td><td>$240 – $420</td><td>Smeg offset gauge, panel-weight adjusted</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Condenser fan motor replacement</td><td>$260 – $440</td><td>Column and larger FAB</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Main control board (newer FAB)</td><td>$420 – $680</td><td>Electronic-control generations</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Compressor replacement (post-warranty)</td><td>$900 – $1,600</td><td>FAB size and refrigerant-dependent</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Color-matched exterior panel</td><td>Quoted individually</td><td>4–8 week Guastalla factory lead</td></tr>
      </table>
      <p class="small">
        Broader refrigerator cost reference: our <a href="/price-list/refrigerator-repair-cost/">refrigerator repair
        cost guide</a>. Built-in-specific scope: <a href="/services/built-in-refrigerator-repair/">built-in
        refrigerator repair</a>. Smeg dishwasher, range, and cooking repair covered on sibling pages, see the Smeg
        <a href="/brands/smeg/">brand hub</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Service areas, where our Smeg calls come from</h2>
      <div class="area-grid">
        <div>
          <h4>Vintage-modern / design-forward</h4>
          <p>Silver Lake · Echo Park · Los Feliz · Venice · Atwater Village · Highland Park · Mount Washington</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Westside (entertainment-space FABs)</h4>
          <p><a href="/beverly-hills/">Beverly Hills</a> · Bel Air · <a href="/brentwood/">Brentwood</a> · <a href="/santa-monica/">Santa Monica</a> · <a href="/west-hollywood/">West Hollywood</a></p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Coastal / pool-house kitchens</h4>
          <p><a href="/malibu/">Malibu</a> · <a href="/pacific-palisades/">Pacific Palisades</a> · Venice · Marina del Rey · Manhattan Beach</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Hollywood Hills contemporary</h4>
          <p>Hollywood Hills · Laurel Canyon · Nichols Canyon · Mount Olympus · Outpost Estates</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>San Fernando Valley + San Gabriel Valley</h4>
          <p><a href="/encino/">Encino</a> · Sherman Oaks · Tarzana · Calabasas · <a href="/pasadena/">Pasadena</a> · South Pasadena · La Cañada</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Ventura + Orange County</h4>
          <p><a href="/thousand-oaks/">Thousand Oaks</a> · Westlake Village · Newport Beach · Newport Coast · Laguna Beach</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Related Smeg and Italian-brand pages</h2>
      <ul class="related-links">
        <li><a href="/brands/smeg/">Smeg brand hub, dishwasher, range, built-in cooking →</a></li>
        <li><a href="/brands/bertazzoni-refrigerator-repair/">Bertazzoni refrigerator repair (Italian sibling from Guastalla) →</a></li>
